    <project_details>
        <title>Urban Heat Island Mitigation via Vertical Solar Arrays</title>
        <problem_statement>
            Current urban solar installations often fail to account for localized heat 
            accumulation, which reduces photovoltaic efficiency by up to 15% during 
            peak summer months in high-density areas.
        </problem_statement>
        <methodology>
            The project will utilize a network of IoT thermal sensors and 
            computational fluid dynamics (CFD) modeling to analyze airflow 
            patterns around skyscraper-mounted panels.
        </methodology>
        <start_date>2026-06-01</start_date>
        <duration_months>24</duration_months>
    </project_details>

